<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-568-422  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 568 422.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Journal of Systems Management  June 1990 v41 n6 p29(6).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Design and development of small data management systems.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gutierrez, Oscar.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The design and development of smaller types of applications, suchas financial analysis and modeling, administration reporting, anddepartmental data management, can be enhanced by using adiscipline that permits its users to gradually mold a workingmodel that considers all aspects of the application.andP;  The end useris usually the owner of the system to be developed and should takean active role in designing the system.andP;  Project breakdown andscheduling for a small data management system can be based on themutual understanding of all participants.andP;  The data managementdevelopment technique used has four phases: project initiation,where the team members get to know each other; analysis of theapplication, which looks at identification of entities,identification of relationships, description of identifiers andattributes, and development of a data model; system design, wherethe physical shape of the system is determined; and systeminstallation, where the system functions as an experimentalworking model until it becomes the final product.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Data ManagementEnd UsersSystem DesignApplications Programming.andO;Feature:   illustrationcharttable.andO;Caption:   Small application development technique. (chart)Small systems application development tools. (table)Data model. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>